# 🛒 NeuralRetail AI — Retail Intelligence System

**Amdox Internship Project**

> A retail analytics platform I built module by module — from raw transaction
> data to a working AI system that forecasts demand, segments customers,
> optimizes inventory, and recommends products.

---

## Why I built it this way

When I started this internship, the brief was simple: *"turn raw retail
transaction data into something a business can actually act on."* That's a
vague goal, so before writing a single line of code I broke it down into the
question a retail business actually asks, in the order they'd ask it:

1. What's happening in my business right now? → **Dashboard / EDA**
2. What do my customers, products, and time patterns look like? → **Feature Engineering**
3. Which customers are valuable, and which are about to leave? → **Customer Intelligence & Churn**
4. What will I sell next month? → **Demand Forecasting**
5. How much stock should I hold, and what's at risk of running out? → **Inventory Optimization**
6. What should I recommend to a customer at checkout? → **Recommendation Engine**
7. Can I trust any of this? → **Model Performance**

That order is also the build order — each module depends on the one before
it, so I treated the project as a pipeline rather than seven separate
scripts:

```
Raw Sales Data
      │
      ▼
Data Cleaning & EDA
      │
      ▼
Feature Engineering  ──────────────► Customer / Product / Time / Country features
      │
      ▼
Customer Segmentation & Churn
      │
      ▼
Demand Forecasting
      │
      ▼
Inventory Optimization
      │
      ▼
Recommendation Engine
      │
      ▼
Streamlit Dashboard  (Executive Overview → Model Performance)
```

I kept this dependency chain in mind at every stage: nothing downstream
gets built until the data feeding it is clean and trustworthy.

