## A note on how I approached this

I didn't build this as seven unrelated ML projects in one repo. Every
module was built to answer a question the previous module raised, and the
git history reflects that — EDA → feature engineering → customer
intelligence → forecasting → inventory → recommendations → dashboard →
model performance, in that order, each one building on clean output from
the last. That's the thinking behind the folder structure too: it's meant
to be read top-to-bottom as a pipeline, not browsed at random.
